# 💸 SpendingTracker

A mobile app to track your daily expenses, built with React Native and Expo.

## Features

- ➕ **Add Expenses** — quickly log what you spent with a category and note
- ✏️ **Edit & Delete** — tap any expense to edit, long press to delete
- 📅 **Filter by Date** — view expenses by Today, This Week, This Month, or All
- 💰 **Budget Limit** — set a monthly budget and get warned when you're close
- 📊 **Charts** — see your spending breakdown by category and last 7 days
- 📤 **Export to Excel** — share your spending report via WhatsApp, email, etc.
- 🔔 **Notification Shortcut** — tap the persistent notification to quickly log an expense

## Categories

- 🍔 Food
- 🎮 Entertainment
- 🛍️ Shopping
- 🚗 Transport
- 📦 Others

## How to Use

### Adding an Expense
1. Tap the **+** button at the bottom right
2. Enter the amount in RM
3. Add an optional note
4. Select a category
5. Tap **Save Expense**

### Editing an Expense
- Tap any expense in the list to edit it

### Deleting an Expense
- Long press any expense to delete it

### Setting a Budget
1. Tap the **💰 Budget** button at the top right
2. Enter your monthly budget in RM
3. A progress bar will show how much you've used
4. You'll get a warning at 80% and when exceeded

### Exporting to Excel
1. Tap the **📤 Export** button at the top right
2. Choose where to share (WhatsApp, email, etc.)

### Notification Shortcut
- A persistent notification stays in your notification bar
- Tap **➕ Log Expense** to quickly log without opening the app

## Installation (Android)

1. Download the latest APK from the releases section
2. Enable "Install from unknown sources" on your Android phone
3. Install the APK
4. Open the app and allow notification permission

